Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.40,1:01:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,perfect timing. Uh we'll probably all go\Ntogether if you know certain cataclysmic
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.79,1:01:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,things happen. So, there's no point to\Nworry about it. That okay,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.88,1:01:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> we all die together. Everybody for it.\NYay.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.48,1:01:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Anybody want to stay here after we\Nall leave?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.72,1:01:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody want to hang in? We've all left.\NIsn't that a strange thing when you
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.59,1:01:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,reconexualize it, you realize, I don't\Nwant to be the only one left to hear out
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.59,1:02:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of everybody here? No way. I don't want\Nto be the only one left here. No.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.92,1:02:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So love then that love then brings us\Ntogether and the mutuality of that field
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.59,1:02:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of love is what we don't want to leave.\NSee you don't want to be left alone on a
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.55,1:02:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,desert island and the steamship goes\Naway with everybody except you
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.55,1:02:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and we have all these things to\Naccomplish while we're here. I've been
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.44,1:02:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,busy living through all this karma. I\Ntold you all the physical ailments and I
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.72,1:02:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,forgot the I had so many of them. I\Ncan't remember them all. I forgot
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.31,1:02:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,breaking my back. That was that was sort\Nof anesus too.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.07,1:02:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you I lifted something and my\Nback collapsed. Three vertebrae
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.52,1:02:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,collapsed.\N>> And uh Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.48,1:02:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Skunk.\N>> Lifting a skunk. Yes. Well, yes. It was
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.28,1:02:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a skunk trap. And I lifted the\Nskunk trap and I felt this shrieking
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.04,1:03:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,pain down my back.\Nthree vertebrae collapsed
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.16,1:03:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,osteoporosis. So, you pick up things uh\Nfrom the collective. I thought, well,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.83,1:03:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never held in mind, you know, you\Ntend to manifest what you hold in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.16,1:03:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never pictured that men get\Nosteoporosis. You know, I was pictured
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.24,1:03:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,little bent old ladies. You know, when I\Ngrew up, there was all little bend over
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.40,1:03:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,ladies and they all had severe\Nosteoporosis and kyphosis. And uh so I
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.48,1:03:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,never thought of a sale man. So it\Nwasn't something I was personally
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.59,1:03:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,holding in mind. So that means you're\Nalso somewhat subject
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.72,1:03:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to what is being held in the collective\Nconsciousness. So instead of berating
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.59,1:03:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself for some kind of negative\Nexperience and thinking, boy, I must
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.03,1:03:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,have bad karma or something, it can be\Nsomething you've picked up from from the
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.44,1:03:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,collective and uh\Nthat helps you bear some things. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.88,1:04:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can we often pick up from the\Ncollective and and experience it out for
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.31,1:04:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the sake of all of us here resist. All\Nright. So
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.11,1:04:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,when we're all together, you realize\Nwhen you look into the eyes of anybody,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.07,1:04:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody in the group, if God said to\Nyou, would you go through some agony so
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.52,1:04:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that she would bear have to bear less?\NYou would say yes, wouldn't you? you
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.03,1:04:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,would just automatically sort of say\Nyes. Why? Because love knows no
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.88,1:04:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,boundaries. So for the sake of a loved\None and spirit, there's no higher love
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.55,1:04:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,than spiritual love. Out of spiritual\Nlove, you would you would I agree. Yes,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.68,1:04:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I would. I would bear that for that\Nperson. And because you're doing it
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.40,1:04:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,voluntarily, it's willing.\NSo if you allow any kind of suffering in
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.76,1:04:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,your life to be voluntary, you've\Nalready eliminated 90% of the suffering.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.72,1:04:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest is purely physical.\NBut the the suffering is really the
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.83,1:05:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,mental anguish. It's isn't it? It's the\Nanguish. The anguish.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.11,1:05:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I drove myself up\Nup the road with this busted back. And
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.03,1:05:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,uh\Noh god. Uh it was the anguish that I
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.64,1:05:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,wasn't going to get there. I didn't know\Nif the body would hang in long enough or
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.03,1:05:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I might pass out in on 89A trying to get\Nto the hospital. So although the pain
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.48,1:05:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,was severe, it was really the anguish of\Nyour capacity to handle it and then the
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.68,1:05:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,situation in which you're in.\NSo you can look at pain and suffering
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.16,1:05:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and death in in in different ways. It\Nbecomes recontextualized and now you say
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.07,1:05:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,can you bear you know can you bear the\Nphysicality for a a period of time?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.44,1:05:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you can bear the physicality. It's\Nthe anguish that that you make that
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.92,1:05:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,makes it seem unbearable. So, it isn't\Nthe pain, it's the anguish that it's
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.16,1:05:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,going to last forever. It's never going\Nto come to an end, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.31,1:06:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When all hope is gone, yeah, that that's\Ncharacteristic of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.92,1:06:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In the depths of hell, there is no hope.\NAbandon all hope, ye who enter here.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.40,1:06:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And you enter agony forever.\NOh Christ. It's not the agony, although
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.24,1:06:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that is severe. It's the forever. And\Nyou begin to experience out what
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.52,1:06:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,eternity is. And eternity is\Nforeverness. And with no hope, with no
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.16,1:06:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,hope ever.\NAnd that's the agony of hopelessness.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.35,1:06:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So it is our hope in how we\Ncontextualize an experience that makes
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.11,1:06:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it either excruciating or bearable.\NExcruciating or bearable.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.40,1:06:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The physicality can be handled. And of\Ncourse I've explained how to handle
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.40,1:06:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,physicality. The way I handle all these\Nthings that ailed me at various times
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.72,1:07:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,was constantly not labeling it and\Nletting go, resisting it. Constantly
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.40,1:07:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,letting go, resisting it. And as you do\Nthat, you get closer and closer to the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.68,1:07:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,source of the pain or the discomfort\Nand you stop labeling it. You don't call
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.28,1:07:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it gastritis or migraine or whatever.\NYou just let go, resisting the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.55,1:07:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,sensation, whatever the sensation is.\NAnd by constantly letting go,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.16,1:07:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,resisting it, you\Nyou transcend it. Yeah. You overcome it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.11,1:07:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You could bypass it. It no longer\Nbothers you. So
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.16,1:07:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,if you can let go of your fear of death,\Nyou can let go of fear of anything. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.07,1:07:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,How about your fear of being short and\Nstupid?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.96,1:07:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I got used to it.\NNo, sure. It wasn't stupid. No,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.00,1:08:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but they wouldn't let me on the ball\Nfield, though.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.92,1:08:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The coach would never pass me and the\Nschool doctor would never pass me for
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.72,1:08:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,participatory uh\Nsports. All right, let's see. We're
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.76,1:08:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,down. We're doing the last 99. I think\Nthis is uh this is slide number 99.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.96,1:08:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Uhhuh. That's the last one, correct?\NYes. 99.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.44,1:08:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes.\N>> You were talking about the blocks.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.96,1:08:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah. Okay. So, that that should remove\Nthe blocks then. Uh
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.83,1:08:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and once you remove the box, the way is\Nopen for the miraculous and the
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.19,1:08:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,miraculous really gets quite strong\Naround level as I say around level five
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.52,1:08:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,560 570.\NThe miraculous becomes absolutely
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.88,1:08:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,continuous.\NAll you have to do is hold the thing in
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.08,1:08:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,mind and it materializes. You're driving\Ndown the road in the old truck
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.52,1:09:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh I think the water pump was\Nfalling off. You need
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.48,1:09:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I had it wired on. I don't know why it\Nfell off. And anyway,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.40,1:09:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,so to correct it, I needed a pair of\Npliers. Well, you wouldn't believe in
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.75,1:09:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that whole truck with all the car I had\Nin there, I could not find a pair of
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.52,1:09:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,pliers. So I said to the guy with me, I\Nsaid, "All we need is a pair of pliers."
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.40,1:09:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And 20 foot ahead of us on the right\Nhand side of the highway was a pair of
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.44,1:09:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,pliers. Nei were they a pair of pliers.\NThey were brand new, never used pair of
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.44,1:09:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,pliers.\NThat kind of thing was just continuous.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.67,1:09:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Just when you run out of water, uh you\Npull up next to something and and uh you
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.75,1:09:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,see that there's a pump handle behind it\Nand it's just miraculous. A car breaks
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.48,1:09:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,down a million miles from nowhere. And\Nthat happened to me a number of times.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.64,1:09:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh the old truck would break down in\Nstrange places. Nobody knew I was even
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.48,1:10:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,there. And some old pal from years ago\Nwould suddenly drive out of nowhere and
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.64,1:10:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,come up and say, "Hey, you've broken\Ndown here. You need help?" Yep.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.80,1:10:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if I I told you one time I\Nwas down near the Mexican border and
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.12,1:10:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,when I first came out, I drove all over\Nthe place with my truck getting used to
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.48,1:10:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the Wild Wild West, you know.\Ndown near the Mexican border and it was
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.12,1:10:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,super hot\Nand uh there's nothing in any direction,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.84,1:10:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, if you get down just north of\Nthe Mexican border.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.64,1:10:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Patagonia\N>> near Patagonia. Yeah. Right. Uhhuh. But
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.32,1:10:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,there's places where, you know, for 50\Nyard miles there's nothing. And uh so I
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.52,1:10:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,pulled the truck in someplace and uh it\Ndied and smoke shot out. Oh, smoke. It
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.36,1:10:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,was a fire under the hood.\NHere's the fire under the hood. I'm a
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.04,1:10:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,million miles an hour nowhere and the\Nsmoke is going up. The whole cab is full
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.36,1:10:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of smoke\Nand uh it's hopeless. You wouldn't be
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.04,1:11:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,able to walk anywhere. I mean, you\Nwouldn't get more than a quarter mile on
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.96,1:11:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that heat with no water. And uh so I\Nthought, well, you're leaving now. So I
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.80,1:11:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,sat back and waited to leave. And\Nyou got to die sometimes. So why not
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.88,1:11:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,now? So I'm I'm sitting there waiting to\Nleave. It's okay with me to go. Every
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.44,1:11:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,time I've been okay to go, it never\Nhappens. I What I should do is resist
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.60,1:11:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it.\NNow I'm not going.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.96,1:11:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I would sit back and say, "Well, if you\Ngo, so you go. You're not going to be
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.88,1:11:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,able to walk for water and the machine's\Non fire. So what can you do?" Then a
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.12,1:11:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,little voice inside my head,\Ndidn't come from elsewhere. was from
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.15,1:11:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,within said uh it had a paper cup with\Nabout this much coffee in the bottom. It
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.56,1:11:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,says take this paper cup. Now in the\Nbottom of the glove compartment is made
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.12,1:12:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of heavy duty cardboard. Says take a\Nscrewdriver and jam it through there. So
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.84,1:12:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I took a screwdriver and I jammed it\Nthrough the cardboard in the bottom of
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.44,1:12:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the glove compartment. And then the\Nknowingness, it wasn't a voice, it was a
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.76,1:12:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,knowingness. The knowingness was to pour\Nthat through the hole, which I did. And
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.32,1:12:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it went like that. And that was the\Nelectrical fire. And the hole was
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.19,1:12:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly over. And the electrical\Napparatus in my old truck, which is
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.19,1:12:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,still very bad.\NMany years of amateur electrical wiring
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.04,1:12:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is a rat's nest. You'd never find in\Nthere using the intellect or the your
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.44,1:12:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,brain where the fire was coming from.\NBut there it was exact. So, I was a
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.36,1:12:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,little disappointed.\NI thought I was out of here. But, uh,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.56,1:12:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that put the fire out and uh, so I\Ndidn't leave then. Anytime I was ready
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.40,1:12:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to leave, something similar would\Nhappen. And I said, I've had it happen
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.80,1:13:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,right in the middle of a lecture walking\Ndown the aisle. And, uh, it's like
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.12,1:13:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,invitational\Nlevel 600. From 600 up, it's it recurs.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.92,1:13:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh it's like invitational. It's like\Na very open welcome door and you have an
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.67,1:13:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,okay, you've got permission to walk\Nthrough.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.96,1:13:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You never know what's going to happen.\NAnd uh so if the body walks on I guess
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.88,1:13:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that was the karmic momentum to do so\Nand fulfill your obligation to Doug to
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.19,1:13:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,God that he gave you certain information\Nand it's your obligation to uh teach
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.48,1:13:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,others with what you have learned. Yeah.\NSo you accept that that's that is to go
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.92,1:13:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,on and that it's not finished yet. So\Nthat's what keeps you going is because
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.32,1:13:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you're fulfilling some karmic propensity\Nand even an agreement I almost I
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.80,1:13:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,remember agreement beforehand in fact\Nthat you're feeling a certain contract
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.52,1:14:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and obligation. Yeah. To uh a group of\Nspirits you might say a group of souls
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.67,1:14:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you know like we all have a certain\Ncommitment to each other. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.15,1:14:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So everybody uh ready to go die any old\Ntime? Are we ready to go together?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.23,1:14:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll give it the old gung-ho when it's\Ntime to go, man. We're just going to
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.84,1:14:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,hold everybody else in mind and give it\Nthe old college cheer.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.36,1:14:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Boom. Off we go a light.\NTrumpet sounding on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.64,1:14:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Here comes that wonderful group from\NSedona.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.84,1:14:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They hang the stones up. Oh, they're\Nback. They're back there. They're back.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.23,1:14:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Happy times are here again.\NWell, in heaven, they get tired of the
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.12,1:15:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,long faces, you know. They get tired of\Nthe sackcloth and ashes type. You know,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.04,1:15:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,something to break up with the monotony\Nthe sin and guilt and sackcloth and
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.44,1:15:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,ashes crowd. You see, sin and guilt and\Nself-rrimation and penance and all that
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.80,1:15:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is at the bottom of the chart and joy\Nand happiness is at the top of the
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.67,1:15:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,chart. Seeking God as you wallow around\Nin guilt.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.19,1:15:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh so guilt as Buddhism says is uh\Nself-indulgent.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.08,1:15:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Guilt is a self-indulgence.\NAnd so instead of feeling good about
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.23,1:15:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,thrashing yourself, now you can feel\Nguilty about feeling guilt.
